  <p style="font-family: Google Sans; font-size: 20px; color: white;">Small changes or additions in the design change the 'IMPACT' of the design.</p></div><br><br><br><br><br><br>

<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br></div>

<h3 style="text-align: center;padding: 150px; font-size: 50px;">Using these insights and lenses, I proceeded to give a Second Thought to a product that I consumed almost everyday during the time I used to attend the class.<br><br>
  The aim was to look beyond the product I was consuming, into the back-end processes of it and find these hidden truths.<br><br><br><br><img src="raw.png" width="1000" height="600"></h3>

<h3 style="text-align: center; padding: 150px;">RAW Pressery is a product that sells a range of cold-pressed fruit juices. I've been a customer of this product since the beginning of this year, and almost every alternate session of this studio was done with a RAW juice or drink next to me.<br><br>I consumed this product a lot over this month, without ever questioning why I'm choosing this over other such products. 'What has got me hooked onto this?','What do I find fascinating about this product?', 'Is it really healthy for me?' were just some of the questions I encountered when I started thinking about this.<br><br><br>Thus I decided to give 'Second Thoughts' to this product.<br>
  </h3><br>



<style>
  .column {
    padding: 60px;
  float: left;
  width: 50%;
}

/* Clear floats after the columns */
.row:after {
